title.narrative: Increased efficiency of customs through increased number of Customs points with non-intrusive control methods financed by the Loan
Hours to clear merchandise from the moment it arrives to Custom terminal until it is released
% increase of web-processed transactions in Customs
Stronger planning, budgeting, treasury, and accounting systmems are in place, in line with international standards

baseline.value: SAFI I does not allow for program based budgeting and payments are processed through a quasi TSA in a separate system

target.value: The agreed revised scope of the SAFI II system is fully developed and ready to be launched. It includes program based budgeting,payment processing throughthe Treasury Single Account.

actual.value: The functional design of SAFI II is greatly advanced and the detailed design of the following modules is close to 90%: budgetformulation and human resources budget planning. Treasury and Security System module is 100%. In addition to that, the detaileddesign of the public investment module is also very advanced (96.4%). 29% of SAFI II, core financial systems, has been developedusing the detailed definitions of the system.

title.narrative: Development of the new SAFI II module for Budget Execution that will include program-based budgeting

baseline.value: The current SAFI I system doesn’t include proper budget execution controls and only allows for line item budgeting

target.value: A new module for Budget Execution in SAFI II that includes program based budgeting has been developed.

actual.value: The functional design of the budget formulation module has allowed the definition of 92% of the expected uses cases of this module,and 76% of the uses case are finalized for the budget execution corresponding module. DINAFI has already started the IT developmentof the budget formulation module, which is in 50% with most of the budget catalogues ready. As of 84 government institutions(central government, decentralized institutions, public companies and institutions not included in the Budget Law), 67 already havea complete programmatic structure, which represents 145 programs. The remaining 17 institutions are expected to have defined theirprogrammatic structure by July 2015.

title.narrative: Implementation of training and dissemination initiatives to strengthen Government transparency, citizen participation, and access to public information

target.value: 22 initiatives have been implemented. Institutional capacity of the government is strengthened and knowledge about right ofaccessto public information and Government transparency tools has increased among public servants and the general public.

title.narrative: Increased capacity in budget planning and formulation through the new integrated financial system (number of training sessions)
